        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 26 at 4:47PM EDT until June 26 at 5:15PM EDT by NWS Mount Holly NJ</headline>
        <description>At 447 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Fleetwood, or 9
miles northeast of Reading, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to vehicles is possible. Wind damage to roofs,
siding, trees, and power lines is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Allentown, Emmaus, Quakertown, Kutztown, Fleetwood, Laureldale, East
Greenville, Topton, Bally, Bechtelsville, Lyons, Zionsville, Ancient
Oaks, Geryville, Gilbertsville, Boyertown, Pennsburg, Mount Penn,
Macungie, and Red Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
